cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with computer vision and robotics, specifically with the problem of matching line segments in stereo sequences. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of L1-minimization, which is a common technique in machine learning and optimization, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of geometric constraints, which could suggest it belongs to cs.GR (Graphics). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of the proposed method for Visual Odometry (VO), which is a common application in robotics, suggesting it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper mentions the use of a benchmarked point and line based VO algorithm, which could suggest it belongs to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
